      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index prediction versus in vitro measurement",
      "description": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) compared against in vitro hemolysis measurements across 5 operating conditions. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all conditions. Variability in experimental hemolysis measurements (CV ≈ 12% across three independent test runs) is discussed in the uncertainty section in prose; the biological scatter and donor-to-donor variability in erythrocyte fragility represent aleatory sources that are acknowledged but not linked to a formal uncertainty quantification artifact for this result.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/morrison/uq/uq-03-hemolysis-epistemic-model-form"
